      <accessrestrict id="aspace_arest">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The collection is open to researchers by appointment. There are no restricted materials in the collection. Please contact the <ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://www.library.yale.edu/musiclib"
                 show="new">Special Collections staff</ref> to schedule an appointment.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_d1e217">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The collection was established in the Music Library of Yale University by the Estate of Frank Bozyan after 1965.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <userestrict id="aspace_urest">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The collection is the physical property of the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University. Copyrights belong to the composers and authors, or their legal heirs and assigns.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_cite">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Misc. Ms. 146, Organ Music from the Estate of Frank Bozyan in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by composer.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of 16 organ works, 1 song, and 1 piece for piano by Frank Bozyan and his friends and colleagues. 12 of the works are holograph scores. The remaining 6 works are photocopies of the composers' holographs.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bh1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Hagop Frank Bozyan was born in 1899. He studied organ at the Yale School of Music, where he received the B.M. degree in 1920. He joined the faculty that year, and continued to teach at Yale until 1965, the year of his death.</p>  
      </bioghist>
